I am a watchman. On the 18th of November, in the morning, about half after four, a man came to me, and informed me that a man had brought into his house a looking-glass, and afterwards, as he believed, some linen, because it was white;
John Negus
and I went about eight in the morning, and thrust the door open. The prisoner immediately jumped out of the window; the sheep skins were lying on the bed; the prisoner was secured, and we took him and the skins in a coach to Justice Wilmot's; the skins were afterwards delivered into the hands of Negus, who has had them ever since I believe .
